-- ft.page: `packages table`

This table contains information about all the packages that we are serving.

-- ft.code:
lang: py

class Package(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(
        unique=True, help_text="name of the FPM package", max_length=255
    )
    base = models.CharField(help_text="git url of FPM package", max_length=1023)
    hash = models.CharField(
        null=True, blank=True, help_text="latest deployed hash of git", max_length=512
    )
    plan = models.CharField(
        help_text="We have different plans like free, paid for serving FPM package",
        max_length=255,
    )
    hours = models.IntegerField(default=0)
    status = models.CharField(
        help_text="status of the package", max_length=255, choices=package_status
    )
    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)
    updated_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now=True)

-- ft.h1: `hash`

This is the commit hash that is currently deployed.

-- ft.h1: `base`

The github, gitlab or bit buket URL that we can clone from or can download
individual files.

-- ft.h1: `plan`

We have the following plans for now:

-- ft.h2: `free`

These plans would be cleaned up every hr if they are idle. Also they will get
18 hrs per day max.

-- ft.h2: `paid`

These plans will not be cleaned up when idle.


